spring. If you're not feeding them enough and they

03:56.439 --> 03:59.844
start eating oak buds. I saw the first herd 
affected. Again, it was Ralph Ballinger's caves

04:04.129 --> 04:08.235
out north of Henderson. I've also seen people cut 
timber in spring and summer and the cattle have...

04:17.712 --> 04:25.082
perhaps not quite as much grass as they want, so 
they go out there and eat all of the oak leaves on

04:17.712 --> 04:25.082
these trees. And they can get down and die. Mary 
Kelly lost four or five cows one year when she was

04:27.205 --> 04:33.033
selling oak timber. So you must be careful that you 
don't let your cattle eat too many oak leaves Oak

04:39.835 --> 04:43.619
buds in the spring are too many acorns. In the fall 
of the year, if you turn your cattle into a pasture

04:43.999 --> 04:54.030
with a lot of acorns on the ground and they get 
started eating them, it seems like that they like

04:43.999 --> 04:54.030
acorns. And if you don't feed them hay and get them 
off of those acorns, if they stay in a woods pasture

04:54.931 --> 05:04.241
