cow. They knew that she was down and couldn't get 
up. She was paralyzed. They would feel of her tail,

06:18.008 --> 06:23.754
find a soft spot due to a deficiency, and call it 
hollow tail. They would split the tail and put

06:24.675 --> 06:29.421
something like salt and pepper or turpentine on 
it. Then, of course, if they treated the cow

06:30.342 --> 06:36.689
properly with enough food and water, a few of them 
would live. Another very common thing in treating

06:37.670 --> 06:40.714
a cow with mineral deficiency we call milk fever 
was seen when a cow would have a calf and sometime

06:41.302 --> 07:07.275
maybe in 48 hours she would become down and unable 
to walk and go into a coma those cattle were

06:41.302 --> 07:07.275
commonly referred to as having milk fever even 
though they didn't have any fever the temperature

06:41.302 --> 07:07.275
would be below normal it was a misnomer and before 
the days of graduate veterinarians who injected

07:07.762 --> 07:20.027
calcium gluconate solution into the vein to make 
the cow overcome the disease and get up and start

07:07.762 --> 07:20.027
walking off in 10 or 15 minutes. The common 
treatment was pumping air into their udder. And,

07:25.075 --> 07:39.388
of course, it would work because it would make the 
cow quit producing milk, and she would gradually

07:25.075 --> 07:39.388
get better, and most of them would survive but end 
up with a case of mastitis, infection up in the

07:25.075 --> 07:39.388
quarters. And the loss of the cud, as people called 
it, when a cow got sick and quit chewing her cud, as

07:40.297 --> 07:59.707
most sick cows do, some people thought they would 
have to take an old dish rag and poke it down their

07:40.297 --> 07:59.707
throat to give them another cud, which, of course, 
